==Trivia==
*Dreykov is not based on any one character from the comics, rather he is an amalgam of various characters. Due to the constant retcons, as well as the vague nature of who exactly ran the Red Room, Dreykov is likely meant to serve as a singular villain to all of the various named Russian agents such as '''Alex Sterelny''', '''Grigor Pchelintsov''' and '''Ivan Petrovich'''.
**His use of pheromones to prevent the Widows from attacking him is similar to that of '''Vassily Ilyich Ulyanov''', an assassin hired to kill Widows who also used a similar perfume. Like Dreykov, Romanoff defeated him by breaking her nose.
*Dreykov was first mentioned in ''[[The Avengers]]'', making him the first main antagonist in an MCU film to be mentioned before his debut, the second being [[Xu Wenwu]] (the "Mandarin") and the third being [[Ego]].

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Ray Winstone]] disliked having to participate in the reshoots for ''[[Black Widow (film)|Black Widow]]'' due to feelings that the film's producers were criticizing his performance. At one point, Winstone considered to leave the project and make [[Marvel Studios]] recast him, but eventually obliged to finish the reshoots to avoid Marvel taking legal action against him if he didn't follow his contract.<ref>[https://www.radiotimes.com/movies/scifi/ray-winstone-soul-destroying-mcu-newsupdate/ Ray Winstone remembers "soul-destroying" experience filming for MCU]</ref>
*[[Adrian McGaw]] and [[Ray Armstrong]] were stunt doubles for [[Ray Winstone]] in the role of Dreykov.

